Hi Fam!!! Please let me introduce myself or reintroduce myself. There’s so many new faces here, and I’d like you to know my story, but more importantly what you will get out of following me🫶

At thirty-four years old, my late husband was diagnosed with cancer. Over the next five years I was his caregiver, while being a mommy to our daughters. In the fall of 2019 Jordan lost his courageous battle and I was forced to start over.

I started this IG and my blog to take you through PARTS of my life that I was going through... exposing what it was like to be a caregiver for my husband at a young age, raising two daughters, being an entrepreneur, and yet still trying to find time for self-care all at the same time.

I’ve chosen to share much of what I’ve gone through because I had NO-ONE to relate to. I often felt VERY alone in my struggles. I just wanted to have a “normal” life. I know how isolating it can be when you are going through big life changes and have no one to relate to! 

I quickly and unexpectedly met my now husband, Adam. I struggled with the feelings of wanting to move forward but also grieving the loss of my prior life and partner. 

Adam and I will be married 2 years in May. We have a blended family with 6 kids and two dogs. 

We are a perfectly imperfect blended family living a perfectly imperfect life.

If there’s anything you take away from my page, it’s this:

1. Never lose hope
2. You deserve happiness
3. SelfCare isn’t selfish 

I would love to know more about you! Please comment below and tell me something about you 🫶

#momsover30 #blendedfamilylove #youngwidow #datingtips #lifeafterloss #singlemomstrong #momssupportingmoms #selfcareisntselfish #selfcareformoms #fortyandfabulous #luckygirlsyndrome

How to not let social media fool you into thinking everyone’s life is perfect…

1. Remember social media only shows a part of someone’s life. It is okay to not want to post every waking minute. 

2. Don’t live your life through people you follow on social media. Get out there and LIVE! 

3. Remember everyone is going through their own journey, and many are fighting battles we can’t even begin to understand. 

4. Life happens to ALL of us 

5. Have compassion for our fellow women who are trying to keep it together despite how hard life has become ♥️

#momsover40 #womenempowerwomen #momswhosupportmoms #selflovewarrior #40andfabulous #over40andfabulous

Sometimes I wish I could just post pictures and not have to have some sort of explanation, or long winded message about life after loss and love after loss. But I can’t do it. I just have too much to share and encourage women and moms who are struggling in their life right now. 

This trip was emotional for me. It is the first time I’ve gone back to my girls camp since losing my first husband and the girls father, Jordan.

A lot has changed in 4 years. A lot. The girls are growing and thriving. I’m remarried. Our family is bigger! More siblings and two doggies too! 

Why is this so meaningful? What does it have to do with you? 

It is a constant message and reminder that you can do hard things. You can make hard decisions. But most importantly, you can find happiness again. It’s a different kind of happiness. A happiness that you will treasure more than anyone because of the heartache you know you endured to achieve it. 

So yes. Visiting Day was amazing. My daughters inspire me every day. But I’m really proud of myself too! It is so true, when it is said life is about the journey and not the destination. That is absolutely the truth.

So thankful for my ♥️ @adampotashapproach every day. 

#loveafterloss #lifeafterloss #newchapterinlife #selflove❤ #youngwidow #lifeisajourneynotadestination #momoftweens #momofdaughters #remarried #secondact #womenempowerwomen

How do you start over and bring someone new into your kids lives? 

This is different for everyone, so there’s no right or wrong way. 

There is only your way. 

It is how you choose to live and keep living after your first partnership has ended. 

I can give you a few tips, that may make the transition easier:) 

1. Must be someone who genuinely likes kids! 

2. Shares similar (not the same values) as you. 

3. Willing to fill the role (not replace) anyone 

4. Trust your own instincts 

5. Don’t obsess over everything 

This is a super tough topic. And one that isn’t spoken about enough. Comment with any questions you have ♥️

#blendedfamilies #bonusdad #momoftweens #lifeafterloss #loveafterloss #lifeadvice #adviceforlife #momsempoweringmoms

👖Here is the perfect CASUAL date night outfit formula for moms over 40👖

First: Make sure you SAVE this reel for outfit inspo for your next casual night out! 

First, you want to have a top that you feel confident in. I was in a funk and I wanted to lift my spirits so on this night, I decided to wear a super bright pink top because when I wear bright colors, it really lifts my mood.

Next, you want to wear a pair of jeans or trousers or pants something that you feel like your butt looks good in. Pants that fit you really well. Wear a pair of jeans that make you feel sexy but also you still feel comfortable because it’s just a casual date night. 

Also, you don’t need to wear high heels to be sexy. If you’re going out on a date but it’s a casual date don’t even bother with high heels. You could do wedges, but on this night we were running out for like a quick sushi dinner, and where we were going was super super casual. So I just opted for a pair of leather flats. 

The perfect date night outfit isn’t so much about wearing a sexy top or a revealing top or spiked heels. It’s really more about your confidence level as a mom and allowing yourself to feel good and confident in what you’re wearing and in your beautiful body! 

If you love this outfit and you want me to send you the links to anything just comment link and I’ll get it sent right over to you! I’m wishing everyone has a better week this week and sending love and peaceful thoughts out to all of my amazing followers XOXO ,

Rachael

40 is a turning point in life. 

It was the moment in my life I realized I deserve the best. It was the moment I realized not everyone who was sitting at my table was there to cheer me on, but to watch me fall. 

It was when I realized I’m the creator of what comes next for my daughters and I.

At one point, i thought my life was over but now I realize it’s just getting started. 

I hope this inspires you to keep going and know that you deserve the best.

The first step to putting together a really good basic, but chic outfit is having a pair of denim that you feel comfortable in but that also fits you really well. They’re not too tight but they’re also not too big.  If you have a similar body like mine, I really really recommend @motherdenim 

I found these available on their website in another color. I’m actually ordering them in blue too! 

Add any basic T-shirt and some fun but classic accessories. Merry Christmas!!! Sharing a little something about me with you guys…

I didn’t grow up with Christmas despite the fact that I was one of the only Jewish kids in my town. 
I always wanted Christmas and I always felt left out.
Fast forward to 30 years later… i happen to meet a man in my second chapter of life @adampotashapproach who has somehow shown me the magic of Christmas! 

Adam, you are pure magic. Making this holiday special not only for my daughters, but for me❤️

From the elf, to the surprises, the holiday lights, to the excitement you have for our family, all our kids, and just the wonderment of it all. 

Watching my girls get to experience what I never had is just pure joy. Thank you. I love you. 

And for those of you who are struggling with anything right now. Keep your chin up. Never lose hope. There is always something wonderful about to happen. Believe in magic.

Day 1 out of 7 days of chic errand outfits for moms over 40…

There’s always gonna be days where you can’t change from your gym OOTD to another outfit. Let’s be honest. We’re moms. We’re busy.  And we don’t have all the time in the world especially for outfit changes AND getting a workout in! 

When I want to look chic, but still have to wear my gym, OOTD I like to focus on a monochromatic look paired with a stylish jacket usually a denim one.

Let me know if you like this series, as I think most of my outfits are actually errand outfits. But if you want links, just comment with the word errand below and I’ll send you links to every single thing that I’m wearing here. 

That being said, I don’t want you to feel like you have to go out and purchase anything I post. This is to give you an idea of an easy outfit to replicate from pieces you already own that are in your closet.

Pick out a pair of leggings and a top that are the same color at a denim jacket and your favorite sneakers boom 💥 You’re good to go run your errands mama!
